11
00:01:26,460 --> 00:01:27,161
Am I right?

12
00:01:30,564 --> 00:01:32,900
What do you have to
offer Mr. Alderton.

13
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:33,634
Well.

14
00:01:39,506 --> 00:01:40,708
You're an old man Mr Lee.

15
00:01:44,578 --> 00:01:45,746
But you and your
little Sheila here,

16
00:01:45,779 --> 00:01:49,950
you can find you
some island, retire.

17
00:01:49,983 --> 00:01:54,988
I take the whole operation,
move it across the pond.

18
00:01:55,021 --> 00:01:57,958
[laughter]

19
00:01:57,991 --> 00:02:01,862
A man who has lived his
entire life in Hong Kong

20
00:02:01,895 --> 00:02:05,366
