23
00:02:14,074 --> 00:02:14,775
Poor?

24
00:02:17,377 --> 00:02:18,846
Pathetic?

25
00:02:18,879 --> 00:02:19,680
Good day Mr. Alderton.

26
00:02:26,853 --> 00:02:28,622
I'm afraid it's
not that easy mate.

27
00:02:35,095 --> 00:02:36,797
You see my boss,
he tell me to come

28
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:40,901
over and take your operation,
no matter what the cost.

29
00:02:44,738 --> 00:02:50,244
So I guess negotiations
had just broken down, huh?

30
00:02:50,277 --> 00:02:54,148
[gun shots]

31
00:02:56,249 --> 00:03:00,121
[screams]

32
00:03:24,578 --> 00:03:27,080
I think it's time to
contact our American friends.

33
00:03:30,984 --> 00:03:34,254
[music playing]

34
00:06:15,348 --> 00:06:18,752
[cheering]

35
00:06:39,272 --> 00:06:40,140
It's no good Paulie.

36
00:06:43,076 --> 00:06:43,777
Don't start this kid.

37
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:49,783
I fought hard to get here.

38
00:06:49,816 --> 00:06:52,486
We fought hard.

39
00:06:52,519 --> 00:06:54,287
We have.

40
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:57,758
And now we take the fall.

41
00:06:57,791 --> 00:07:01,862
Like the man said,
it ain't your night.

42
00:07:01,895 --> 00:07:02,596
It's not right.

43
00:07:05,799 --> 00:07:06,500
Right.

44
00:07:09,269 --> 00:07:10,470
I've been doing this
so long, I don't

45
00:07:10,503 --> 00:07:11,672
know what right is anymore.

46
00:07:16,342 --> 00:07:17,478
You really telling me that?

47
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:26,486
Nah.

48
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:28,588
I know what right is.

49
00:07:28,621 --> 00:07:30,757
Right is you fighting pro.

50
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:34,027
It's scum like Mr
Lee behind bars.

51
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:35,228
You know what right is?

52
00:07:35,261 --> 00:07:38,198
Maybe it's the commies not
taken over in Hong Kong.

53
00:07:38,231 --> 00:07:41,535
And maybe it's petrol
at $0.60 a gallon.

54
00:07:41,568 --> 00:07:42,636
Yeah.

55
00:07:42,669 --> 00:07:43,770
That's what right is.

56
00:07:46,539 --> 00:07:48,675
When was the last time
you bought a gallon of gas?

57
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,010
That's what I mean.

58
00:07:50,043 --> 00:07:52,546
It ain't right.

59
00:07:52,579 --> 00:07:55,882
But that's the way it is.

60
00:07:55,915 --> 00:07:58,919
Listen to me Shane.

61
00:07:58,952 --> 00:08:01,688
You don't cross these people.

62
00:08:01,721 --> 00:08:05,025
You cross them, you're dead.

63
00:08:09,028 --> 00:08:11,498
All right.

64
00:08:11,531 --> 00:08:12,266
I'll be a good boy.

65
00:08:36,422 --> 00:08:38,391
Relax my boy.

66
00:08:38,424 --> 00:08:39,793
Tonight is your night.

67
00:08:54,307 --> 00:08:57,778
Mr Lee.

68
00:08:57,811 --> 00:09:00,881
[inaudible], I thought
it was hot in Vegas

69
00:09:00,914 --> 00:09:03,283
until I came over here, Mr. Lee.

70
00:09:03,316 --> 00:09:07,788
Don Nicholas, you hone
my humble fight arena.

71
00:09:07,821 --> 00:09:09,221
Pleasure's all mine.

72
00:09:09,255 --> 00:09:12,091
And please, call me Uncle Nicky.

73
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:15,629
Nobody calls me Don anymore,
except maybe the Feds, huh.

74
00:09:15,662 --> 00:09:18,332
[laughter]

75
00:09:28,641 --> 00:09:30,477
MR LEE: I appreciate
you coming all the way.

76
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:31,477
Don't mention it.

77
00:09:31,511 --> 00:09:33,480
You know, if this
works out, there's

78
00:09:33,513 --> 00:09:36,516
going to be plenty of money
on the table for both of us.

79
00:09:36,549 --> 00:09:38,985
Ah.

80
00:09:39,018 --> 00:09:41,154
May I present Abdul.

81
00:09:41,187 --> 00:09:44,591
He's going to win
the contest tonight.

82
00:09:44,624 --> 00:09:46,526
When?

83
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:47,828
What do you mean,
these fights are fixed?

84
00:09:50,964 --> 00:09:51,832
They better be. huh.

85
00:09:51,865 --> 00:09:54,534
[laughter]

86
00:09:55,535 --> 00:09:58,471
I'm just pulling your chain.

87
00:09:58,504 --> 00:10:00,606
And the other fighter?

88
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:03,577
He's, uh, how do you call?

89
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:04,811
Resigned.

90
00:10:04,844 --> 00:10:05,946
Yeah.

91
00:10:05,979 --> 00:10:08,514
He's resigned to his fate.

92
00:10:08,548 --> 00:10:14,019
Well as you would
say, the fix is in.

93
00:10:14,053 --> 00:10:14,755
Yeah.

94
00:10:17,824 --> 00:10:21,228
[cheers]

95
00:10:29,335 --> 00:10:31,071
OK, ladies and gentlemen.

96
00:10:31,104 --> 00:10:33,373
This is the moment
you've all been

97
00:10:33,406 --> 00:10:35,542
waiting for-- main event time.

98
00:10:35,575 --> 00:10:38,879
Abdul, Abdul Sabbah,
where are you mate?

99
00:10:38,912 --> 00:10:39,980
Come on down.

100
00:10:40,013 --> 00:10:40,780
He's mean.

101
00:10:40,813 --> 00:10:42,082
He's fierce.

102
00:10:42,115 --> 00:10:44,683
He's a super fresh killer
all the way from the streets

103
00:10:44,717 --> 00:10:46,887
of Morocco, the Amazing Abdul!

104
00:10:58,564 --> 00:11:00,967
And in this corner.

105
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:01,967
He's wild.

106
00:11:02,001 --> 00:11:03,103
He's crazy.

107
00:11:03,136 --> 00:11:08,875
Our very own Hong Kong
lost boy, Shane McQuade!

108
00:11:08,908 --> 00:11:12,245
[cheers]

109
00:11:19,052 --> 00:11:22,355
Gentlemen, there's
only one rule.

110
00:11:22,388 --> 00:11:24,490
That's fight like men.

111
00:11:24,524 --> 00:11:26,426
I know you can do that.

112
00:11:35,001 --> 00:11:38,372
[bell rings]

113
00:11:47,146 --> 00:11:47,914
Damn.

114
00:11:47,947 --> 00:11:48,849
That was fast.

115
00:11:53,419 --> 00:11:54,888
Was that fast?

116
00:11:54,921 --> 00:11:56,323
Because it felt fast.

117
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:42,702
You make it too easy.

118
00:12:42,735 --> 00:12:47,173
These boys are good Mr
Lee, best in the business.

119
00:12:47,206 --> 00:12:49,075
How do you find them?

120
00:12:49,108 --> 00:12:51,011
The slums of every city.

121
00:12:51,044 --> 00:12:55,281
It's just a matter of selection.

122
00:12:55,314 --> 00:12:56,483
Natural selection, huh.

123
00:12:56,516 --> 00:12:58,718
Like, uh, how do you call them?

124
00:12:58,751 --> 00:12:59,519
Evolution.

125
00:12:59,552 --> 00:13:02,154
Yeah, evolution.

126
00:13:02,188 --> 00:13:03,790
Survival of the fittest.

127
00:13:51,003 --> 00:13:53,973
How you doing kid?

128
00:13:54,006 --> 00:13:54,708
Never better.

129
00:13:58,144 --> 00:14:00,046
Keep it cool out there.

130
00:14:00,079 --> 00:14:02,415
Don't let them get to you Shane.

131
00:14:02,448 --> 00:14:04,317
You hear me?

132
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:05,118
Yeah.

133
00:14:05,151 --> 00:14:07,520
I can hear you.

134
00:14:07,553 --> 00:14:09,822
Watch that temper.

135
00:14:09,856 --> 00:14:13,259
You only got two rounds to go.

136
00:14:13,292 --> 00:14:16,663
You can make it.

137
00:14:16,696 --> 00:14:19,231
[bell rings]

138
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:34,880
Oh yeah.

139
00:14:46,893 --> 00:14:47,827
Oh yeah.

140
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:48,827
You know what?

141
00:14:48,861 --> 00:14:52,298
It's almost nap time.

142
00:14:52,331 --> 00:14:54,801
Good night.

143
00:14:54,834 --> 00:14:57,770
Aw, you want Mommy
to tuck you in?

144
00:14:57,803 --> 00:14:59,239
Is that what you want?

145
00:14:59,272 --> 00:15:02,876
Aw no you don't.

146
00:15:02,909 --> 00:15:04,510
I guess you ain't got a Mommy.

147
00:15:04,544 --> 00:15:08,281
All you got is that old,
drunk freak in the corner.

148
00:15:08,314 --> 00:15:09,082
Isn't that right?

149
00:15:23,095 --> 00:15:26,032
The white kid's got a
real flair for drama.

150
00:15:26,065 --> 00:15:28,968
He's quite a-- how
do you call it?

151
00:15:29,001 --> 00:15:29,869
Performer.

152
00:15:29,902 --> 00:15:31,504
Performer, yeah.

153
00:15:31,537 --> 00:15:33,873
He's a regular Meryl Streep.

154
00:15:33,906 --> 00:15:35,242
You'd almost think
there was no fix in.

155
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:58,064
Son of a--

156
00:16:03,135 --> 00:16:06,105
1.

157
00:16:06,138 --> 00:16:08,608
2.

158
00:16:08,641 --> 00:16:10,109
3.

159
00:16:10,142 --> 00:16:12,579
4.

160
00:16:12,612 --> 00:16:15,081
5.

161
00:16:15,114 --> 00:16:17,083
6.

162
00:16:17,116 --> 00:16:20,587
Why'd you kill him man?

163
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:23,255
7.

164
00:16:23,289 --> 00:16:23,990
8.

165
00:16:28,094 --> 00:16:30,063
9.

166
00:16:30,096 --> 00:16:34,067
9 comes after 8.

167
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:38,238
You don't know about
the [inaudible] you made.

168
00:16:38,271 --> 00:16:39,038
9.

169
00:16:39,071 --> 00:16:39,872
10.

170
00:16:39,905 --> 00:16:42,909
And the winner, Shane McQuade!

171
00:16:42,942 --> 00:16:43,876
[crowd repeatedly chants shane]

172
00:16:50,349 --> 00:16:52,285
Come on kid, we're out of here.

173
00:16:52,318 --> 00:16:53,786
Relax Paulie,
can't you hear them?

174
00:16:53,819 --> 00:16:54,688
They love Me!

175
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:05,098
Yeah I can.

176
00:17:05,131 --> 00:17:06,566
Come on.

177
00:17:06,598 --> 00:17:11,069
I got to tell you Mr Lee,
I'm a little disappointed.

178
00:17:11,103 --> 00:17:12,572
This kind of thing
is totally, uh--

179
00:17:12,605 --> 00:17:13,839
Unacceptable.

180
00:17:13,873 --> 00:17:16,542
Yeah, unacceptable,
especially if we're

181
00:17:16,575 --> 00:17:19,479
going to consider picking up
your franchises in the States.

182
00:17:19,511 --> 00:17:22,548
Please accept my
humble apologies.

183
00:17:22,581 --> 00:17:25,018
If there is anything I
can do to make it up?

184
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:29,289
I'll think of something.

185
00:17:33,693 --> 00:17:40,199
Until then, I'll
be at the hotel.

186
00:17:40,232 --> 00:17:42,201
Good night.

187
00:17:42,234 --> 00:17:45,605
[non english speech]

188
00:17:55,214 --> 00:17:57,282
Come on kid, move it.

189
00:17:57,316 --> 00:17:59,252
We got to get out of here.

190
00:17:59,285 --> 00:18:02,655
You probably have to leave town.

191
00:18:02,688 --> 00:18:04,857
Look, there's a name
and address, Alia.

192
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:07,293
She'll get you out of this.

193
00:18:07,326 --> 00:18:08,127
What's got into you?

194
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:08,895
It was only one fight.

195
00:18:20,306 --> 00:18:22,008
Look, I'm sorry I blew it.

196
00:18:22,041 --> 00:18:23,842
But he called you
a drunk Paulie.

197
00:18:23,876 --> 00:18:25,310
I am a drunk Shane.

198
00:18:25,344 --> 00:18:26,946
Not anymore.

199
00:18:26,979 --> 00:18:29,048
Not so much.

200
00:18:29,081 --> 00:18:32,352
And anyway, the crowd loved it.

201
00:18:32,385 --> 00:18:36,422
Mr Lee wouldn't do anything to
harm his most popular fighter.

202
00:18:36,455 --> 00:18:41,394
Can he still be so naive even
after years of your training?

203
00:18:41,427 --> 00:18:44,597
He's just a hot
tempered kid Mr Lee.

204
00:18:44,630 --> 00:18:46,833
I'll, I'll get him into line.

205
00:18:46,866 --> 00:18:47,633
I promise.

206
00:18:47,666 --> 00:18:49,001
I'm sorry Mr Lee.

207
00:18:49,034 --> 00:18:51,204
I, I just got mad.

208
00:18:51,237 --> 00:18:53,539
You have to learn control.

209
00:18:53,572 --> 00:18:56,743
I thought maybe Paulie
would teach it to you.

210
00:18:56,776 --> 00:18:57,844
Perhaps he still can.

211
00:19:03,883 --> 00:19:05,985
You're quite right
about one thing.

212
00:19:06,018 --> 00:19:08,954
I can't injure my
most popular fighter.

213
00:19:08,988 --> 00:19:14,394
If I cannot hurt you,
how can I control you?

214
00:19:14,427 --> 00:19:15,194
No!

215
00:19:15,227 --> 00:19:17,764
Shut up Shane.

216
00:19:17,797 --> 00:19:20,666
[gun cocking]

217
00:19:22,735 --> 00:19:25,605
[gun shot]

218
00:19:40,553 --> 00:19:45,091
I'm sorry I brought
you here kid.

219
00:19:45,124 --> 00:19:46,426
You got to get away.

220
00:19:46,459 --> 00:19:48,361
You gotta go.

221
00:19:48,394 --> 00:19:49,729
No Paulie, no.

222
00:19:49,762 --> 00:19:51,630
I'm going to stay here with you.

223
00:19:51,664 --> 00:19:53,633
No.

224
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,600
No.

225
00:19:55,634 --> 00:19:57,170
You, you gotta get away.

226
00:19:57,203 --> 00:19:57,904
Go.

227
00:20:05,611 --> 00:20:06,579
That was an avoidable accident.

228
00:20:12,451 --> 00:20:14,487
See what your rashness
has brought on?

229
00:20:22,795 --> 00:20:23,796
Good.

230
00:20:23,829 --> 00:20:26,264
These are the fruits of anger.

231
00:20:26,298 --> 00:20:28,701
Remember this.

232
00:20:28,734 --> 00:20:30,069
Don't worry.

233
00:20:30,102 --> 00:20:30,804
I will remember this.

234
00:20:41,447 --> 00:20:42,215
No.

235
00:20:42,248 --> 00:20:42,949
You'll hit me.

236
00:20:46,252 --> 00:20:47,520
Look's like we're
going to have to end

237
00:20:47,553 --> 00:20:48,388
this another time Mr Lee.

238
00:21:46,445 --> 00:21:47,914
[whistle blowing]

239
00:21:47,947 --> 00:21:50,016
[knocking]

240
00:21:50,049 --> 00:21:50,750
[inaudible]

241
00:21:53,852 --> 00:21:57,723
[non english speech]

242
00:21:57,756 --> 00:21:58,658
Go away.

243
00:22:04,663 --> 00:22:06,532
Will you just get the
bloody door already?

244
00:22:10,769 --> 00:22:11,471
Ow!

245
00:22:19,445 --> 00:22:24,349
Bitch, why don't
you get the door.

246
00:22:24,383 --> 00:22:25,351
[knocking]

247
00:22:25,384 --> 00:22:26,919
Who is it?

248
00:22:26,952 --> 00:22:28,753
SHANE: Friend of Paulie's.

249
00:22:28,787 --> 00:22:31,090
Well come on back later
friend of Paulie's.

250
00:22:31,123 --> 00:22:33,192
SHANE: It's an emergency.

251
00:22:33,225 --> 00:22:35,895
Paulie knows I never
do business before dark.

252
00:22:35,928 --> 00:22:37,830
Let him hold your
hand until them.

253
00:22:37,863 --> 00:22:41,000
I'm just going to go lay down.

254
00:22:41,033 --> 00:22:41,734
SHANE: Paulie's dead.

255
00:22:51,076 --> 00:22:52,778
He told me you could help me.

256
00:22:52,811 --> 00:22:55,781
I need to get out of Hong Kong.

257
00:22:55,814 --> 00:22:56,683
Come on in.

258
00:23:01,153 --> 00:23:04,891
[airplane engines]

259
00:23:05,958 --> 00:23:07,360
OK.

260
00:23:07,393 --> 00:23:08,160
I'm in.

261
00:23:08,193 --> 00:23:08,895
Where do you want to go?

262
00:23:11,697 --> 00:23:13,132
I don't know?

263
00:23:13,165 --> 00:23:15,568
Oh, that's not very helpful?

264
00:23:15,601 --> 00:23:17,837
How about Australia?

265
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:18,938
Why Australia?

266
00:23:18,971 --> 00:23:20,673
You always want to send
people to Australia.

267
00:23:20,706 --> 00:23:22,408
Nobody wants to go there.

268
00:23:22,441 --> 00:23:23,476
It's nice there.

269
00:23:23,509 --> 00:23:24,477
No it's not.

270
00:23:24,510 --> 00:23:26,045
It's hot and dusty.

271
00:23:26,078 --> 00:23:27,213
It's got snakes.

272
00:23:27,246 --> 00:23:28,547
You haven't even been.

273
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:29,582
Of course I have.

274
00:23:29,615 --> 00:23:30,950
Oh yeah when?

275
00:23:30,983 --> 00:23:31,983
Well, it's been--

276
00:23:32,017 --> 00:23:35,221
I have a friend in
America, Las Vegas.

277
00:23:38,257 --> 00:23:41,127
Nothing direct to Vegas.

278
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:43,029
Now how about Los Angeles?

