01:09:40,316 --> 01:09:41,084
Look.

834
01:09:41,117 --> 01:09:42,752
I already told him.

835
01:09:42,785 --> 01:09:44,754
I'm not fighting anymore.

836
01:09:44,787 --> 01:09:45,688
Come on, come on.

837
01:09:45,720 --> 01:09:48,825
At least just talk
to the guy, OK?

838
01:09:48,858 --> 01:09:51,227
One last time, before you go.

839
01:09:51,260 --> 01:09:53,062
Maybe he can convince you.

840
01:09:53,095 --> 01:09:54,130
Oh, Jason.

841
01:09:54,163 --> 01:09:55,865
For me.

842
01:09:55,898 --> 01:09:57,133
Just do me this one favor.

843
01:09:57,166 --> 01:09:59,736
Talk to the man, OK?

844
01:09:59,769 --> 01:10:01,438
Then you can, you
can go your own way.

845
01:10:06,375 --> 01:10:07,977
All right.

846
01:10:08,010 --> 01:10:10,547
I'll talk to him.

847
01:10:10,580 --> 01:10:11,514
Great.

848
01:10:11,547 --> 01:10:12,249
Follow me.

849
01:10:17,820 --> 01:10:20,757
62,300.

850
01:10:20,790 --> 01:10:22,759
Yeah.

851
01:10:22,792 --> 01:10:24,259
Thanks.

852
01:10:24,293 --> 01:10:27,130
Bye bye.

853
01:10:27,163 --> 01:10:29,065
Look Mr Bender, I'm good.

854
01:10:29,098 --> 01:10:29,866
I won't fight.

855
01:10:29,899 --> 01:10:31,567
I've had enough of it.

856
01:10:31,601 --> 01:10:34,037
I came in here as a
favor to Jason, but--

857
01:10:34,070 --> 01:10:36,239
No buts.

858
01:10:36,272 --> 01:10:41,144
What's going to happen if
I call the police, Vinnie?

859
01:10:41,177 --> 01:10:43,079
Or should I say Shane?

860
01:10:43,112 --> 01:10:46,483
I recognized you the minute you
walked through the front door.

861
01:10:46,516 --> 01:10:48,884
Go ahead, call them.

862
01:10:48,918 --> 01:10:50,887
I'll be gone.

863
01:10:50,920 --> 01:10:52,121
They'll never catch me.

864
01:10:52,154 --> 01:10:54,457
And neither will you.

865
01:10:54,490 --> 01:10:56,559
Well I think I've got
somebody here that'll make you

866
01:10:56,592 --> 01:10:58,194
change your mind about that.

867
01:10:58,227 --> 01:10:59,563
Get in here fellas.

868
01:11:03,199 --> 01:11:05,634
Well, well, well.

869
01:11:10,439 --> 01:11:12,875
If it isn't little boy lost.

870
01:11:18,681 --> 01:11:22,018
How you doing in Vegas momma?

871
01:11:22,051 --> 01:11:24,020
It's a little hot for me.

872
01:11:24,053 --> 01:11:25,488
Nah.

873
01:11:25,521 --> 01:11:26,956
It's going to get hotter.

874
01:11:26,989 --> 01:11:28,258
Who are these guys?

875
01:11:28,291 --> 01:11:30,159
You didn't tell me
anything about this.

876
01:11:30,192 --> 01:11:32,529
Jason, meet Abdul.

877
01:11:32,562 --> 01:11:35,599
Second rate fighter,
a third rate hood.

878
01:11:38,434 --> 01:11:40,336
ABDUL: Pleasure.

879
01:11:40,369 --> 01:11:43,239
This changes nothing Marks.

880
01:11:43,272 --> 01:11:45,475
You can put a dozen of these
guys between me and the door,

881
01:11:45,508 --> 01:11:48,244
I'm still walking out of here.

882
01:11:48,277 --> 01:11:49,979
We'll see.

883
01:11:50,012 --> 01:11:51,381
This is crazy.

884
01:11:51,414 --> 01:11:53,483
Nah.

885
01:11:53,516 --> 01:11:57,020
It's going to get crazier.

886
01:11:57,053 --> 01:11:57,820
Run.

887
01:11:57,853 --> 01:11:59,256
Get the hell out of here.

888
01:12:03,326 --> 01:12:07,263
Get the hell out of here.

889
01:12:07,296 --> 01:12:10,667
[gun shot]

890
01:12:13,436 --> 01:12:14,203
[gun shot]

891
01:12:14,236 --> 01:12:16,673
SHANE: No!

892
01:12:16,706 --> 01:12:20,076
[gun shots]

893
01:12:25,514 --> 01:12:26,416
Aw man.

894
01:13:11,027 --> 01:13:12,996
[inaudible] drive faster, now.

895
01:13:13,029 --> 01:13:14,431
I'm going, I'm going.

896
01:13:23,005 --> 01:13:23,973
Aw yeah.

897
01:13:24,006 --> 01:13:25,475
Catch him up, damn it.

898
01:13:25,508 --> 01:13:26,409
Catch him!

899
01:13:52,501 --> 01:13:54,470
[inaudible]!

900
01:13:54,503 --> 01:13:55,405
Shoot him.

901
01:14:11,520 --> 01:14:15,424
[gun shots]

902
01:14:17,026 --> 01:14:20,930
[gun shots]

903
01:14:25,000 --> 01:14:26,169
Slow down.

904
01:14:26,202 --> 01:14:26,969
[inaudible]

905
01:14:27,002 --> 01:14:27,904
I got you.

906
01:14:41,517 --> 01:14:45,422
[tires squealing]

907
01:14:56,532 --> 01:14:57,967
Don't worry.

908
01:14:58,000 --> 01:14:59,969
I won't hurt you that much.

909
01:15:00,002 --> 01:15:02,972
Thank you.

910
01:15:03,005 --> 01:15:04,974
[tires squealing]

911
01:15:05,007 --> 01:15:08,912
[gun shots]

912
01:15:35,538 --> 01:15:39,375
[gun shots]

913
01:15:55,324 --> 01:15:57,293
Are you OK?

914
01:15:57,326 --> 01:15:58,695
They told me Jason was dead.

915
01:16:04,233 --> 01:16:15,211
[phone ringing]

916
01:16:15,244 --> 01:16:17,346
BENDER (ON PHONE): Is it done?

917
01:16:17,379 --> 01:16:18,548
Yeah.

918
01:16:18,581 --> 01:16:21,617
It's done you son of a bitch.

919
01:16:21,650 --> 01:16:23,419
I've got two of your
men down over here.

920
01:16:23,452 --> 01:16:24,921
Why don't you come and get them?

921
01:16:24,954 --> 01:16:26,756
I've got a better
idea hot shot.

922
01:16:26,789 --> 01:16:28,558
Why don't you come
here and just give up?

923
01:16:28,591 --> 01:16:29,926
No, no, no.

924
01:16:29,959 --> 01:16:32,428
Why would I do a
thing like that?

925
01:16:32,461 --> 01:16:33,629
ANGELIQUE (ON PHONE):
Help me Shane.

926
01:16:33,662 --> 01:16:35,998
He'll kill me.

927
01:16:36,031 --> 01:16:38,968
Please, help me.

928
01:16:39,001 --> 01:16:40,069
Tell you what.

929
01:16:40,102 --> 01:16:41,938
Lets just call a truce.

930
01:16:41,971 --> 01:16:43,339
You lost your friend.

931
01:16:43,372 --> 01:16:45,408
I've lost some friends.

932
01:16:45,441 --> 01:16:47,777
And let's just leave
it at that, all right?

933
01:16:47,810 --> 01:16:49,779
So what's the deal?

934
01:16:49,812 --> 01:16:51,480
I'll stop gunning
for you and I'll

935
01:16:51,513 --> 01:16:55,618
give you Angelique if you agree
to do one last bout for me.

936
01:16:55,651 --> 01:16:57,687
We'll split the take,
go our separate ways.

937
01:17:02,057 --> 01:17:03,259
All right.

938
01:17:03,292 --> 01:17:05,361
If that's what it's going
to take to end this,

939
01:17:05,394 --> 01:17:08,097
I'll see you in an hour.

940
01:17:08,130 --> 01:17:09,432
Here.

941
01:17:09,465 --> 01:17:11,334
I have a friend who
lives out by Hoover Dam.

942
01:17:11,367 --> 01:17:12,368
All right, that will do.

943
01:17:12,401 --> 01:17:13,903
You stay there until
you hear from me.

944
01:17:13,936 --> 01:17:14,871
What if I don't?

945
01:17:14,904 --> 01:17:16,638
You will.

946
01:17:16,672 --> 01:17:20,576
One way or another, you will.

947
01:17:20,609 --> 01:17:21,544
You know how to use this?

948
01:17:21,577 --> 01:17:22,345
Yeah.

949
01:17:22,378 --> 01:17:24,547
You taught me, remember?

950
01:17:24,580 --> 01:17:26,515
That's right.

951
01:17:26,548 --> 01:17:29,018
Look, we better get moving.

952
01:17:29,051 --> 01:17:30,518
Good luck.

953
01:17:30,552 --> 01:17:31,454
You too.

954
01:18:15,564 --> 01:18:18,301
Relax Mr McQuade.

955
01:18:18,334 --> 01:18:21,037
Tonight, you will make
us very much money.

956
01:18:21,070 --> 01:18:22,438
Yeah.

957
01:18:22,471 --> 01:18:25,473
Boy, the suckers really paid to
see a fugitive murder suspect

958
01:18:25,507 --> 01:18:28,143
fighting, on pay per view.

959
01:18:28,177 --> 01:18:30,913
What an angle.

960
01:18:30,946 --> 01:18:32,348
What about Angelique?

961
01:18:35,951 --> 01:18:40,056
Son, we have over a million
dollars in advance promotions.

962
01:18:40,089 --> 01:18:43,259
And that even counting
the side bets.

963
01:18:43,292 --> 01:18:45,593
You all right?

964
01:18:45,627 --> 01:18:48,064
Oh, she's fine.

965
01:18:48,097 --> 01:18:51,100
And ain't nobody
going to bother her

966
01:18:51,133 --> 01:18:53,502
as long as you're a good boy.

967
01:18:53,535 --> 01:18:57,139
Yeah, you are going
to be a good boy,

968
01:18:57,172 --> 01:18:59,607
aren't you Mr McQuade?

969
01:18:59,641 --> 01:19:03,178
I think Mr McQuade
has learned his lesson.

970
01:19:03,212 --> 01:19:05,013
He seems almost--

971
01:19:05,047 --> 01:19:05,748
Contrite.

972
01:19:09,752 --> 01:19:12,588
[laughter]

973
01:19:27,970 --> 01:19:29,638
Good evening.

974
01:19:29,671 --> 01:19:32,708
Tonight I'd like to say
welcome and thank you

975
01:19:32,741 --> 01:19:35,578
to all the beautiful
memories of our exclusive,

976
01:19:35,611 --> 01:19:38,647
closed circuit pay
per view system.

977
01:19:38,680 --> 01:19:41,851
For tonight, I'm
going to bring to you

978
01:19:41,884 --> 01:19:44,587
a most awesome
spectacle, unavailable

979
01:19:44,620 --> 01:19:45,822
from your local cable operator.

980
01:19:48,457 --> 01:19:53,963
You see, a week ago, in
another ring in Hong Kong,

981
01:19:53,996 --> 01:19:57,867
in the aftermath,
two men lie dead.

982
01:19:57,900 --> 01:20:01,337
And what is the cause?

983
01:20:01,370 --> 01:20:05,241
Shane McQuade,
formerly of Hong Kong,

984
01:20:05,274 --> 01:20:08,677
and currently
Interpol's most wanted.

985
01:20:08,710 --> 01:20:13,215
Tonight, he's rematched against
the same fighter he faced

986
01:20:13,248 --> 01:20:17,319
and defeated before
that bloody massacre.

987
01:20:17,352 --> 01:20:22,124
I'm talking about the Moroccan
public enemy number one,

988
01:20:22,157 --> 01:20:26,595
until he found a
hobby, kickboxing.

989
01:20:26,628 --> 01:20:28,965
The dreaded Abdul Sabbah!

990
01:21:05,601 --> 01:21:07,203
Tonight's the night.

991
01:21:07,236 --> 01:21:08,137
Yeah it is.

992
01:21:25,821 --> 01:21:28,424
This time, it's for real.

993
01:22:04,626 --> 01:22:05,328
Huzzah!

994
01:23:24,473 --> 01:23:25,174
All right!

995
01:23:32,247 --> 01:23:33,915
Uh huh.

996
01:23:33,949 --> 01:23:34,650
Yeah.

997
01:24:10,686 --> 01:24:14,090
[bell rings]

998
01:24:22,164 --> 01:24:22,865
What the hell is this?

999
01:24:25,634 --> 01:24:26,335
[inaudible].

1000
01:24:33,408 --> 01:24:36,344
Yeah

1001
01:24:36,378 --> 01:24:40,115
This is stupid Abdul.

1002
01:24:40,148 --> 01:24:41,884
Are you a fighter or a killer?

1003
01:24:41,917 --> 01:24:45,219
We're both killers.

1004
01:24:45,253 --> 01:24:46,422
If I win--

1005
01:24:46,455 --> 01:24:47,990
If you win, they're going
to throw you in the ring

1006
01:24:48,023 --> 01:24:50,159
with another killer.

1007
01:24:50,192 --> 01:24:51,626
These people are maniacs!

1008
01:24:54,696 --> 01:24:56,098
This has got to end.

1009
01:24:59,701 --> 01:25:01,603
There's only one
way for this to end.

1010
01:25:04,673 --> 01:25:08,577
[sound of swords clanging]

1011
01:25:42,611 --> 01:25:43,512
And now you die.

1012
01:26:04,566 --> 01:26:08,471
[sound of sword falling]

1013
01:26:22,184 --> 01:26:23,519
It's all over now.

1014
01:26:23,552 --> 01:26:24,319
It's finished.

1015
01:26:24,352 --> 01:26:25,587
This is the end.

1016
01:26:25,620 --> 01:26:26,322
Finito.

1017
01:26:37,065 --> 01:26:40,602
[gun shots]

1018
01:26:41,503 --> 01:26:44,840
[gun shot]

1019
01:26:48,376 --> 01:26:51,847
Get that helicopter here now.

1020
01:26:51,880 --> 01:26:52,748
They're on their way.

1021
01:26:56,651 --> 01:26:58,387
You've done well.

1022
01:26:58,420 --> 01:27:02,024
You've earned your half.

1023
01:27:02,057 --> 01:27:02,925
Half.

1024
01:27:02,958 --> 01:27:04,826
You're kidding, right?

1025
01:27:04,860 --> 01:27:07,329
Go ahead, take it all kid.

1026
01:27:07,362 --> 01:27:10,232
But remember, you'll be
looking over your shoulder

1027
01:27:10,265 --> 01:27:12,834
for the rest of your life.

1028
01:27:12,868 --> 01:27:15,003
How do you know I'm even
going to let you live?

1029
01:27:15,036 --> 01:27:17,439
[gun cocking]

1030
01:27:17,472 --> 01:27:19,074
I'm a killer.

1031
01:27:19,107 --> 01:27:23,145
You are a killer Mr
McQuade, and a talented one.

1032
01:27:23,178 --> 01:27:25,747
But, not of the cold
blooded variety.

1033
01:27:25,780 --> 01:27:28,984
Two old men, unarmed?

1034
01:27:29,017 --> 01:27:29,818
No.

1035
01:27:29,851 --> 01:27:32,888
You won't do it.

1036
01:27:32,921 --> 01:27:35,356
[gun cocks]

1037
01:27:35,390 --> 01:27:38,826
[laughter]

1038
01:27:38,860 --> 01:27:40,395
Good luck kid.

1039
01:27:40,428 --> 01:27:44,366
Until we meet again.

1040
01:27:44,399 --> 01:27:48,268
[gun shot]

1041
01:27:51,339 --> 01:27:54,810
[gun shot]

1042
01:27:54,843 --> 01:27:57,213
[gun shots]

1043
01:27:59,314 --> 01:28:02,183
[dogs barking]

1044
01:28:29,344 --> 01:28:31,780
Shane.

1045
01:28:31,813 --> 01:28:33,782
What happened to you?

1046
01:28:33,815 --> 01:28:37,719
I killed a few people.

1047
01:28:37,752 --> 01:28:38,754
This is for you.

1048
01:28:38,787 --> 01:28:40,355
I don't think so.

1049
01:28:40,388 --> 01:28:41,557
Uh uh.

1050
01:28:41,590 --> 01:28:43,792
See, I tailed your ass
all the way from the arena

1051
01:28:43,825 --> 01:28:48,196
because I knew your hands
would touch that dough.

1052
01:28:48,229 --> 01:28:49,698
All a set up, right?

1053
01:28:49,731 --> 01:28:51,900
Right from the start.

1054
01:28:51,933 --> 01:28:54,169
You're a sweet guy Shane.

1055
01:28:54,202 --> 01:28:56,905
Not too smart.

1056
01:28:56,938 --> 01:28:58,340
Yeah, I've heard that.

1057
01:29:01,176 --> 01:29:01,877
You want the money?

1058
01:29:05,046 --> 01:29:05,814
Here.

1059
01:29:05,847 --> 01:29:06,715
Here it is.

1060
01:29:30,705 --> 01:29:32,541
Sorry Shane.

1061
01:29:32,574 --> 01:29:34,910
I had to play along until now.

1062
01:29:34,943 --> 01:29:36,078
But it's all over now.

1063
01:29:36,111 --> 01:29:37,313
We can go away together
with the money.

1064
01:29:42,384 --> 01:29:43,652
Forget about her.

1065
01:29:43,685 --> 01:29:45,520
She's the past.

1066
01:29:45,553 --> 01:29:46,488
I'm your future.

1067
01:29:46,521 --> 01:29:48,824
I don't think so.

1068
01:29:48,857 --> 01:29:50,692
You said I wasn't very smart.

1069
01:29:50,725 --> 01:29:52,526
Maybe you were right.

1070
01:29:52,560 --> 01:29:53,328
I didn't mean it.

1071
01:29:53,361 --> 01:29:54,396
I was just kidding.

1072
01:29:54,429 --> 01:29:57,699
I'm smart enough to
stay away from you.

1073
01:29:57,732 --> 01:30:00,235
Take a walk Angelique.

1074
01:30:00,268 --> 01:30:01,336
Take a fist full of money.

1075
01:30:01,369 --> 01:30:02,137
Hell, take it all.

1076
01:30:02,170 --> 01:30:05,540
Just go away.

1077
01:30:05,573 --> 01:30:07,441
Uh uh.

1078
01:30:07,475 --> 01:30:10,212
It doesn't work
that way lover boy.

1079
01:30:10,245 --> 01:30:15,417
If you don't come with me
now, you don't go anywhere.

1080
01:30:15,450 --> 01:30:20,889
What can I say, I don't
handle rejection very well.

1081
01:30:20,922 --> 01:30:21,823
Drop the gun.

1082
01:30:24,893 --> 01:30:27,796
[gun shot]

1083
01:30:29,864 --> 01:30:33,268
[gun shot]

1084
01:31:12,107 --> 01:31:14,076
Well.

1085
01:31:14,109 --> 01:31:16,611
I guess it's goodbye again.

1086
01:31:16,644 --> 01:31:19,748
What if I want
to come with you?

1087
01:31:19,781 --> 01:31:20,749
No you don't.

1088
01:31:20,782 --> 01:31:23,152
You need a chance to start over.

1089
01:31:26,421 --> 01:31:27,088
We could start over.

1090
01:31:30,725 --> 01:31:31,727
Shane, I could have got her.

1091
01:31:31,760 --> 01:31:33,028
Why did you stop me?

1092
01:31:38,399 --> 01:31:41,136
A week ago, I killed a man.

1093
01:31:41,169 --> 01:31:42,170
I broke his neck.

1094
01:31:42,203 --> 01:31:46,107
And since then, once
you kill someone,

1095
01:31:46,141 --> 01:31:49,311
your whole world changes.

1096
01:31:49,344 --> 01:31:50,045
You change.

1097
01:31:57,152 --> 01:31:59,454
You were always right.

1098
01:31:59,487 --> 01:32:00,889
You were always late.

1099
01:32:34,489 --> 01:32:37,159
[thunder]

1100
01:32:50,471 --> 01:32:52,941
